title: Question 16
prompt: Each of three camera stores carries three different models of 6-megapixel digital cameras. The prices for the cameras are shown in the chart. Which store has the lowest median price for 6-megapixel digital cameras.
description: Click the <u>one best answer</u> to each question.
feedback: The median is the number that falls in the center of a series of numbers if they are listed in order. In the prices for Cameron’s Cameras, the median is between $125.00. In the prices for Pearson Photography, the median is $113.50. In the prices for Image-I-Nation, the median is $116.99. The lowest median is $113.50, Pearson Photography.
